1
00:00:01,280 --> 00:00:03,480
( singing in Japanese )

2
00:00:03,550 --> 00:00:05,680
♪

3
00:00:32,840 --> 00:00:35,480
♪ PROUD OF MYSELF 

4
00:00:43,220 --> 00:00:45,150
♪

5
00:00:58,570 --> 00:00:59,500
( Eugeo gasps )

6
00:01:04,010 --> 00:01:06,640
Bercouli: THERE. NOW I’M READY.

7
00:01:06,710 --> 00:01:08,410
( Eugeo gasps )

8
00:01:08,480 --> 00:01:12,450
Bercouli: ALL RIGHT, KID,
BEFORE WE GET INTO IT,

9
00:01:12,510 --> 00:01:15,020
THERE’S SOMETHING
I WANNA ASK YOU.

10
00:01:15,080 --> 00:01:16,120
Eugeo: WHAT?

11
00:01:16,180 --> 00:01:18,520
Bercouli: YOU DIDN’T, YOU KNOW,

12
00:01:18,590 --> 00:01:22,790
KILL VICE COMMANDER FANATIO,
DID YOU?

13
00:01:22,860 --> 00:01:25,090
Eugeo: SHE’S ALIVE.

14
00:01:25,160 --> 00:01:27,600
SHE’S BEING HEALED AS WE SPEAK.

15
00:01:27,660 --> 00:01:28,860
( Bercouli sighs )

16
00:01:28,930 --> 00:01:30,130
THAT’S GOOD.

17
00:01:30,200 --> 00:01:31,770
SINCE YOU SPARED HER LIFE,

18
00:01:31,830 --> 00:01:34,540
I’LL RETURN THE FAVOR
AND SPARE YOURS.

19
00:01:34,600 --> 00:01:36,000
( Eugeo gasps )

20
00:01:36,070 --> 00:01:38,010
HOW DISRESPECTFUL.

21
00:01:38,070 --> 00:01:39,640
( Bercouli chuckles )

22
00:01:39,710 --> 00:01:41,440
WHY DO YOU THINK THAT?

23
00:01:41,510 --> 00:01:44,650
Eugeo: IF YOU’RE THIS HIGH UP
IN THE CATHEDRAL,

24
00:01:44,710 --> 00:01:47,650
YOU MUST BE THE COMMANDER
OF THE INTEGRITY KNIGHTS.

25
00:01:47,720 --> 00:01:49,650
Bercouli: YEAH, WHAT IF I AM?

26
00:01:50,820 --> 00:01:52,450
Eugeo: WHAT ABOUT THE OTHERS?!

27
00:01:52,520 --> 00:01:54,490
FANATIO ISN’T THE ONLY KNIGHT!

28
00:01:54,560 --> 00:01:58,930
\h\h\h\hELDRIE, THE FOUR
WHIRLING BLADES, ALICE...

29
00:01:58,990 --> 00:02:01,960
WHAT ABOUT THEM?!
DON’T THEY MATTER?!

30
00:02:02,030 --> 00:02:04,700
\h\h\h\hBercouli: I SEE.
YOU’RE TAKING THAT ROAD.

31
00:02:04,770 --> 00:02:07,000
HOW DO I PUT THIS?

32
00:02:07,070 --> 00:02:09,400
ELDRIE IS ALICE’S APPRENTICE.

33
00:02:09,470 --> 00:02:10,840
THE FOUR WHIRLING BLADES--

34
00:02:10,910 --> 00:02:14,080
DAKIRA, JACE,
HOVEREN, AND GEERO--

35
00:02:14,140 --> 00:02:15,910
THEY’RE FANATIO’S.

36
00:02:15,980 --> 00:02:19,580
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hAND HER? WELL,
SHE HAPPENS TO BE MY APPRENTICE.

37
00:02:19,650 --> 00:02:22,580
\h\h\h\hIT’S NOT THAT I
DON’T CARE ABOUT THE OTHERS.

38
00:02:22,650 --> 00:02:25,990
\h\h\h\hIT’S JUST
I’M INVESTED IN FANATIO.

39
00:02:26,050 --> 00:02:29,820
THAT’S WHY, IF YOU KILLED HER,
I’D BE OBLIGED TO AVENGE HER.

40
00:02:29,890 --> 00:02:31,760
THAT’S ALL THERE IS TO IT.

41
00:02:31,830 --> 00:02:34,830
( chuckles ) THOUGH,
NOW THAT I THINK ABOUT IT,

42
00:02:34,900 --> 00:02:38,470
I GUESS LITTLE ALICE DOES
LOOK UP TO ME AS HER MENTOR.

43
00:02:38,530 --> 00:02:41,670
SHE’S NOT THE SAME
AS SHE WAS SIX YEARS AGO,

44
00:02:41,740 --> 00:02:44,040
WHEN SHE FIRST BECAME
AN APPRENTICE KNIGHT.

45
00:02:44,110 --> 00:02:46,770
IF ME AND HER WENT AT IT NOW,

46
00:02:46,840 --> 00:02:48,880
\h\h\h\hI DON’T KNOW
WHO’D COME OUT ON TOP.

47
00:02:48,940 --> 00:02:50,750
( Eugeo gasps )

48
00:02:50,810 --> 00:02:54,520
Bercouli: ANYWAY, SEEING AS HOW
ALICE IS AS STRONG AS ME,

49
00:02:54,580 --> 00:02:56,850
\h\h\h\hYOU MUST HAVE
SNUCK PAST HER SOMEHOW,

50
00:02:56,920 --> 00:02:59,850
BUT YOU WON’T BE
SO LUCKY WITH ME.

51
00:02:59,920 --> 00:03:02,890
\h\h\h\hCOME TO THINK OF IT,
SHOULDN’T THERE BE TWO OF YOU?

52
00:03:02,960 --> 00:03:05,860
THE PRIME SENATOR
SAID YOU HAD A PARTNER.

53
00:03:05,930 --> 00:03:07,960
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hI GUESS,
IF HE’S NOT HERE WITH YOU,

54
00:03:08,030 --> 00:03:12,370
THAT MEANS HE’S OFF SOMEWHERE
KEEPING LITTLE ALICE BUSY.

55
00:03:12,430 --> 00:03:14,400
Eugeo: YEAH, HE PROBABLY IS.

56
00:03:14,470 --> 00:03:16,710
I’M READY.

57
00:03:16,770 --> 00:03:18,410
LET’S GET THIS OVER WITH.

58
00:03:18,470 --> 00:03:21,080
I’M CURIOUS TO SEE
WHO’LL AVENGE YOU.

59
00:03:21,140 --> 00:03:22,740
( Bercouli chuckles )

60
00:03:22,810 --> 00:03:26,580
\h\h\h\hNO ONE, KID.
I DON’T HAVE A MENTOR.

61
00:03:26,650 --> 00:03:29,120
♪

62
00:03:37,490 --> 00:03:39,760
Eugeo: NORKIA STYLE,
LIGHTNING SLASH.

63
00:03:39,830 --> 00:03:42,130
OR IT’S SOMETHING LIKE IT.

64
00:03:42,200 --> 00:03:44,630
WITH HIS SWORD LIKE THAT,
\h\h\h\hIT’LL TAKE HIM

65
00:03:44,700 --> 00:03:47,140
AN EXTRA MOVE OR TWO
TO ACTIVATE THE TECHNIQUE,

66
00:03:47,200 --> 00:03:50,840
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hBUT IF I USE
THE AINCRAD STYLE’S SONIC LEAP,

67
00:03:50,910 --> 00:03:52,610
I CAN STRIKE HIM FIRST.

68
00:03:54,640 --> 00:03:57,010
\h\h\h\hBercouli: AH, NOW,
THAT’S AN INTERESTING STANCE.

69
00:03:57,080 --> 00:03:59,180
I’VE NEVER SEEN IT BEFORE.

70
00:03:59,250 --> 00:04:00,920
DO YOU USE COMBO ATTACKS?

71
00:04:02,020 --> 00:04:03,380
Eugeo: MAYBE I DO.

72
00:04:03,450 --> 00:04:04,490
MAYBE I DON’T.

73
00:04:04,550 --> 00:04:06,020
WHY DO YOU CARE?

74
00:04:06,090 --> 00:04:08,620
Bercouli: I DON’T. IT’S JUST
THAT THERE WAS A KNIGHT

75
00:04:08,690 --> 00:04:11,860
FROM THE DARK TERRITORY
WHO LIKED TO USE ’EM, TOO.

76
00:04:11,930 --> 00:04:14,600
\h\h\h\hI FOUGHT HIM
A COUPLE OF TIMES BEFORE.

77
00:04:14,660 --> 00:04:17,500
I DIDN’T LIKE THE EXPERIENCE,
TO BE HONEST.

78
00:04:17,570 --> 00:04:19,530
MY STYLE’S SIMPLE.

79
00:04:19,600 --> 00:04:23,110
DOING ALL THEM FLASHY MOVES
IS WAY TOO COMPLICATED.

80
00:04:23,170 --> 00:04:26,740
Eugeo: IS THAT SO? DO YOU
WANT ME TO FIGHT LIKE YOU, THEN,

81
00:04:26,810 --> 00:04:28,840
USING ONLY CONVENTIONAL MOVES?

82
00:04:28,910 --> 00:04:32,780
Bercouli: HELL, NO. YOU WANNA
USE COMBO ATTACKS, GO AHEAD.

83
00:04:32,850 --> 00:04:35,520
\h\h\h\hI CAN HANDLE
ANYTHING YOU DISH OUT, KID.

84
00:04:35,580 --> 00:04:37,690
I SHOULD WARN YOU, THOUGH,

85
00:04:37,750 --> 00:04:40,420
I’M GONNA USE
MY BEST MOVE FIRST,

86
00:04:40,490 --> 00:04:42,490
AND YOU AIN’T READY FOR IT.

87
00:04:43,560 --> 00:04:45,130
( Eugeo gasps )

88
00:04:45,190 --> 00:04:48,000
\h\h\h\hIF HIS SWORD’S
ALREADY IN PERFECT CONTROL,

89
00:04:48,060 --> 00:04:50,130
THEN I’VE ONLY GOT ONE CHANCE.

90
00:04:50,200 --> 00:04:54,640
AS HE ACTIVATES HIS MOVE,
I’LL ATTACK WITH SONIC LEAP.

91
00:04:54,700 --> 00:04:58,670
Bercouli: TASTE THE BLADE
OF BERCOULI SYNTHESIS ONE.

92
00:04:59,870 --> 00:05:01,440
EN GARDE.

93
00:05:01,510 --> 00:05:02,710
Eugeo: BERCOULI?

94
00:05:02,780 --> 00:05:04,010
♪

95
00:05:04,080 --> 00:05:05,910
( chorus vocalizing )

96
00:05:05,980 --> 00:05:06,950
( Bercouli grunts )

97
00:05:07,020 --> 00:05:09,050
( ticking clock slows )

98
00:05:09,120 --> 00:05:11,550
( Eugeo yelling )

99
00:05:13,190 --> 00:05:14,690
( ticking clock slows )

100
00:05:14,760 --> 00:05:17,560
( gasps ) THAT RIPPLE,

101
00:05:17,630 --> 00:05:19,390
IT’S WHERE HE JUST SLASHED.

102
00:05:22,430 --> 00:05:23,670
( groans )

103
00:05:31,610 --> 00:05:33,480
( gasping )

104
00:05:37,550 --> 00:05:40,150
\h\h\h\hBercouli: OOF.
TALK ABOUT CUTTING IT CLOSE.

105
00:05:40,220 --> 00:05:41,750
THE LAST THING I EXPECTED

106
00:05:41,820 --> 00:05:44,920
\h\h\h\hWAS FOR YOU TO COME
RUSHING IN AT ME LIKE THAT.

107
00:05:44,990 --> 00:05:48,620
\h\h\h\hSORRY, KID.
I DAMN NEAR KILLED YOU.

108
00:05:48,690 --> 00:05:52,530
Eugeo: YEAH, I KNOW YOU DID,
BUT WITH WHAT?

109
00:05:52,590 --> 00:05:56,770
Bercouli: THAT WAS MY BEST MOVE,
JUST LIKE I TOLD YOU.

110
00:05:56,830 --> 00:06:00,170
WHEN I TOOK THAT SWING,
I WASN’T JUST SLICING AIR.

111
00:06:00,240 --> 00:06:04,440
I WAS SLICING A MOMENT
IN THE FUTURE, SO TO SPEAK.

112
00:06:04,510 --> 00:06:07,480
Eugeo: SLICING THE FUTURE?

113
00:06:07,540 --> 00:06:10,780
Bercouli: THE FIRST TIME I SAW
A DARK KNIGHT USE A COMBO ATTACK

114
00:06:10,850 --> 00:06:14,580
WAS JUST AFTER I BECAME
AN INTEGRITY KNIGHT MYSELF.

115
00:06:14,650 --> 00:06:18,020
THE SWORD TECHNIQUES I LEARNED
WERE ALL ABOUT PUTTING

116
00:06:18,090 --> 00:06:21,520
AS MUCH STRENGTH AS I COULD
BEHIND A SINGLE STRIKE,

117
00:06:21,590 --> 00:06:24,760
BUT SWORD TECHNIQUES
USING COMBINATION MOVES

118
00:06:24,830 --> 00:06:27,100
FOCUS ON HOW TO HANDLE
YOUR ENEMY’S ATTACKS

119
00:06:27,160 --> 00:06:29,100
AND LAND HITS.

120
00:06:29,160 --> 00:06:33,600
IT’S PRETTY OBVIOUS WHICH
IS MORE PRACTICAL IN A FIGHT.

121
00:06:33,670 --> 00:06:37,570
ANYWAY, I GOT BEAT UP REAL GOOD,
BUT I SURVIVED.

122
00:06:37,640 --> 00:06:39,070
THEN I GOT TO THINKING

123
00:06:39,140 --> 00:06:41,940
HOW I COULD LAND A HIT
AGAINST A COMBO USER.

124
00:06:43,710 --> 00:06:45,950
I FOUND THE ANSWER
WITH THIS THING.

125
00:06:46,010 --> 00:06:51,020
ORIGINALLY IT WAS PART OF
A DIVINE OBJECT CALLED A CLOCK.

126
00:06:51,090 --> 00:06:54,760
IT USED TO HANG ON THE WALL
OF THE CENTRAL CATHEDRAL.

127
00:06:54,820 --> 00:06:57,760
IT WAS HERE WHEN THE WORLD
WAS FIRST CREATED,

128
00:06:57,830 --> 00:06:59,660
OR SO I WAS TOLD.

129
00:07:01,160 --> 00:07:02,830
IT HAD A WEIRD NAME.

130
00:07:02,900 --> 00:07:05,430
\h\h\h\hTHE PONTIFEX
CALLED IT "SYSTEM CLOCK"

131
00:07:05,500 --> 00:07:06,970
OR SOMETHING LIKE THAT.

132
00:07:07,040 --> 00:07:09,800
\h\h\h\hWHEN LITTLE ALICE
USES HER OSMANTHUS BLADE,

133
00:07:09,870 --> 00:07:12,910
\h\h\h\hIT CUTS THROUGH
THE HORIZONTAL AXIS OF SPACE,

134
00:07:12,970 --> 00:07:15,810
\h\h\h\hBUT MINE CUTS
THE VERTICAL AXIS OF TIME.

135
00:07:17,510 --> 00:07:19,510
NOW IT’S GOT A NEW NAME,

136
00:07:19,580 --> 00:07:21,620
THE TIME-SPLITTING SWORD.

137
00:07:22,680 --> 00:07:23,820
Eugeo: WHEN HE SWUNG IT,

138
00:07:23,890 --> 00:07:26,090
THE FORCE OF HIS STRIKE
STAYED IN PLACE.

139
00:07:26,150 --> 00:07:28,990
THAT MEANS I DON’T HAVE
A CHANCE AGAINST HIM UP CLOSE.

140
00:07:30,690 --> 00:07:32,690
I’LL HAVE TO USE
LONG-RANGE ATTACKS.

141
00:07:32,760 --> 00:07:35,530
SYSTEM CALL. CONNECT ARMAMENT.

142
00:07:35,600 --> 00:07:37,430
- SEARCH ARCHIVED MEMORY.
- Bercouli: LET ME GUESS.

143
00:07:37,500 --> 00:07:40,600
YOU’RE SETTING YOURSELF UP TO
ATTACK FROM A DISTANCE, RIGHT?

144
00:07:40,670 --> 00:07:43,740
EVERYONE WHO SEES
THAT MOVE DOES.

145
00:07:43,810 --> 00:07:46,410
SAME GOES FOR ALL
THE INTEGRITY KNIGHTS

146
00:07:46,470 --> 00:07:49,910
\h\h\h\hTHAT CAME AFTER ME,
INCLUDING FANATIO AND ALICE.

147
00:07:49,980 --> 00:07:51,750
ONCE THEY SAW THAT MOVE,

148
00:07:51,810 --> 00:07:53,750
\h\h\h\hTHEY PICKED
LONG-RANGE PERFECT CONTROL

149
00:07:53,820 --> 00:07:55,620
TO TRY AND DEAL WITH IT.

150
00:07:55,680 --> 00:07:56,920
I CAN’T BLAME ’EM.

151
00:07:56,990 --> 00:07:58,620
TRYING TO BRING ME DOWN

152
00:07:58,690 --> 00:08:01,560
GOT TO BE SORT OF
A CONTEST BETWEEN ’EM.

153
00:08:01,620 --> 00:08:04,460
\h\h\h\hBUT I NEVER LOST.
I SPARRED WITH ALL OF ’EM,

154
00:08:04,530 --> 00:08:06,890
\h\h\h\hAND HERE I AM,
STILL THEIR COMMANDER.

155
00:08:09,960 --> 00:08:12,870
WELL, IF ONE OF ’EM
DOES TAKE MY JOB,

156
00:08:12,930 --> 00:08:14,870
IT’LL PROBABLY BE ALICE.

157
00:08:14,940 --> 00:08:18,070
I SURE AM LOOKIN’ FORWARD
\h\h\h\hTO THIS, THOUGH.

158
00:08:18,140 --> 00:08:20,480
I’M CURIOUS TO SEE
WHAT KIND OF MOVES

159
00:08:20,540 --> 00:08:23,110
HELPED YOU GET PAST
ALL THOSE KNIGHTS.

160
00:08:23,180 --> 00:08:25,650
Eugeo: DON’T WORRY. YOU WILL.

161
00:08:26,750 --> 00:08:28,020
( Bercouli chuckles )

162
00:08:28,080 --> 00:08:30,080
COME AND GET IT, KID.

163
00:08:30,150 --> 00:08:33,820
\h\h\h\hTHIS TIME,
I WON’T GO EASY ON YOU.

164
00:08:39,530 --> 00:08:41,830
Eugeo: ENHANCE ARMAMENT!

165
00:08:41,900 --> 00:08:44,570
♪

166
00:08:49,800 --> 00:08:50,740
( Bercouli grunts )

167
00:08:59,150 --> 00:09:00,380
( Eugeo yells )

168
00:09:00,450 --> 00:09:01,620
( Bercouli yells )

169
00:09:01,680 --> 00:09:03,020
( ticking clock slows )

170
00:09:03,080 --> 00:09:05,590
( gasps )

171
00:09:05,650 --> 00:09:08,520
( Eugeo roars )

172
00:09:10,930 --> 00:09:12,530
( Bercouli yelps )

173
00:09:16,530 --> 00:09:17,500
( Eugeo grunts )

174
00:09:17,570 --> 00:09:18,830
( ice shatters )

175
00:09:23,100 --> 00:09:24,040
( Bercouli gasps )

176
00:09:28,080 --> 00:09:29,540
CLEVER.

177
00:09:29,610 --> 00:09:31,650
( Eugeo roars )

178
00:09:33,550 --> 00:09:35,550
BLUE ROSE SWORD...

179
00:09:35,620 --> 00:09:37,520
LEND ME YOUR POWER.

180
00:09:37,590 --> 00:09:40,020
RELEASE RECOLLECTION!

181
00:09:46,560 --> 00:09:48,400
\h\h\h\hCardinal:
NOW PAY CLOSE ATTENTION.

182
00:09:48,460 --> 00:09:51,430
THE PERFECT WEAPON CONTROL ART
HAS TWO STAGES,

183
00:09:51,500 --> 00:09:53,500
ENHANCE AND RELEASE.

184
00:09:53,570 --> 00:09:54,970
Kirito: ENHANCE?

185
00:09:55,040 --> 00:09:57,410
- Eugeo: RELEASE?
- Cardinal: YES.

186
00:09:57,470 --> 00:10:01,480
\h\h\h\hENHANCING AWAKENS
PART OF YOUR WEAPON’S MEMORIES.

187
00:10:01,540 --> 00:10:04,680
\h\h\h\hTHE ACT CAUSES
A NEW ATTACK TO MANIFEST.

188
00:10:04,750 --> 00:10:06,410
IN THE RELEASING STAGE,

189
00:10:06,480 --> 00:10:09,080
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hYOU CAN AWAKEN
ALL OF YOUR WEAPON’S MEMORIES.

190
00:10:09,150 --> 00:10:11,990
THEN YOU CAN UNLEASH
ITS MOST SAVAGE POWER.

191
00:10:12,050 --> 00:10:13,920
Kirito: OH. I GET IT.

192
00:10:13,990 --> 00:10:15,520
♪

193
00:10:19,530 --> 00:10:23,000
THAT EXPLAINS ELDRIE’S WHIP.
IN ITS ENHANCED STAGE,

194
00:10:23,060 --> 00:10:25,830
IT CAN GET LONGER THAN NORMAL
AND THEN SPLIT.

195
00:10:25,900 --> 00:10:28,070
♪

196
00:10:30,670 --> 00:10:32,510
Eugeo: THEN ITS RELEASE STAGE

197
00:10:32,570 --> 00:10:34,540
WAS WHEN IT CHANGED
INTO A SNAKE.

198
00:10:34,610 --> 00:10:36,910
Cardinal: YOU ARE CORRECT.
THAT SAID,

199
00:10:36,980 --> 00:10:39,910
YOU TWO SHOULD AVOID USING
RELEASE FOR THE TIME BEING.

200
00:10:39,980 --> 00:10:42,020
Eugeo: WH-WHY SHOULD WE?

201
00:10:42,080 --> 00:10:44,520
Cardinal: BECAUSE YOU ARE
\h\h\h\hNOT YET READY TO.

202
00:10:44,590 --> 00:10:46,920
\h\h\h\hYOU HAVE ONLY
JUST LEARNED OF THE ART.

203
00:10:46,990 --> 00:10:49,420
UNTIL YOU MASTER IT,
YOU CANNOT CONTROL

204
00:10:49,490 --> 00:10:52,160
THE POWER GENERATED
BY YOUR WEAPON’S MEMORIES,

205
00:10:52,230 --> 00:10:55,730
\h\h\h\hESPECIALLY THOSE
OF A DIVINE OBJECT LIKE YOURS.

206
00:10:55,800 --> 00:10:58,670
IT CAN HARM YOU
AS MUCH AS YOUR ENEMY.

207
00:10:58,730 --> 00:11:02,500
IF YOU’RE NOT CAREFUL,
IT WILL KILL YOU.

208
00:11:04,310 --> 00:11:06,040
( ice crackling )

209
00:11:09,780 --> 00:11:10,880
( Eugeo chuckles )

210
00:11:10,950 --> 00:11:13,050
( Bercouli gasps, chuckles )

211
00:11:13,110 --> 00:11:17,650
I NEVER SAW A SWORDSMAN TOSS
HIS BLADE DURING A FIGHT BEFORE.

212
00:11:17,720 --> 00:11:20,160
\h\h\h\hDID YOU COME UP
WITH THAT TRICK YOURSELF?

213
00:11:20,220 --> 00:11:23,620
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hEugeo: UH-UH.
MY PARTNER TAUGHT ME THAT ONE.

214
00:11:23,690 --> 00:11:26,730
\h\h\h\hTHE BATTLEFIELD
HAS LOTS OF OPPORTUNITIES.

215
00:11:26,790 --> 00:11:28,900
ANYTHING CAN BE
A WEAPON OR A TRAP.

216
00:11:28,960 --> 00:11:30,060
( Bercouli chuckles )

217
00:11:30,130 --> 00:11:33,400
\h\h\h\hMAKE THE BEST
OF WHAT YOU GOT. SMART.

218
00:11:33,470 --> 00:11:36,740
WELL, YOU MIGHT HAVE GOTTEN
THE UPPER HAND THIS ROUND,

219
00:11:36,800 --> 00:11:39,770
BUT THERE’S NO WAY IN HELL
YOU’RE GONNA BEAT ME!

220
00:11:39,840 --> 00:11:41,140
♪

221
00:11:41,210 --> 00:11:42,910
( growling )

222
00:11:42,980 --> 00:11:44,650
( roars )

223
00:11:47,850 --> 00:11:49,620
- ( Eugeo gasps )
- ( Bercouli chuckles )

224
00:11:52,850 --> 00:11:56,830
Eugeo: THE BLUE ROSE SWORD
HAS TWO DORMANT MEMORIES,

225
00:11:56,890 --> 00:11:59,460
ETERNAL ICE AND ROSE.

226
00:11:59,530 --> 00:12:03,770
WHEN I ACTIVATE ETERNAL ICE,
IT FREEZES EVERYTHING.

227
00:12:03,830 --> 00:12:06,470
NOW I’LL SHOW YOU
WHAT ROSE CAN DO.

228
00:12:08,770 --> 00:12:10,740
BLUE ROSE, BLOOM!

229
00:12:14,680 --> 00:12:17,010
( Bercouli gasps )
WHAT’D YOU DO?!

230
00:12:17,080 --> 00:12:19,950
Eugeo: THE ROSES BLOOM
BY ABSORBING THE LIFE

231
00:12:20,010 --> 00:12:22,120
OF THOSE TRAPPED IN THE ICE.

232
00:12:23,350 --> 00:12:24,590
Bercouli: DAMN IT.

233
00:12:24,650 --> 00:12:26,020
YOU LITTLE PUNK.

234
00:12:26,090 --> 00:12:28,320
SO WAS THIS YOUR PLAN ALL ALONG,

235
00:12:28,390 --> 00:12:29,560
KILLING THE BOTH OF US?!

236
00:12:29,620 --> 00:12:31,560
Eugeo: NOT US. JUST YOU.

237
00:12:31,630 --> 00:12:36,200
YOU HAVE AN ADVANTAGE OVER ME
IN EVERY WAY, EXCEPT ONE.

238
00:12:36,260 --> 00:12:38,670
IT’S YOUR TOTAL AMOUNT
\h\h\h\hOF LIFE LEFT.

239
00:12:38,730 --> 00:12:40,670
BASED ON YOUR APPEARANCE,

240
00:12:40,740 --> 00:12:43,610
YOU BECAME AN INTEGRITY KNIGHT
IN YOUR FORTIES,

241
00:12:43,670 --> 00:12:47,240
SO YOUR LIFE VALUE
IS LOWER THAN MINE.

242
00:12:47,310 --> 00:12:51,580
I’M YOUNGER, AND MY LIFE VALUE
IS NEAR ITS PEAK.

243
00:12:51,650 --> 00:12:53,580
EVEN THOUGH YOU LANDED A HIT,

244
00:12:53,650 --> 00:12:56,650
THE LIFE I HAVE LEFT
IS STILL HIGHER THAN YOURS.

245
00:12:56,720 --> 00:12:58,650
THAT’S WHAT I HOPED, ANYWAY.

246
00:12:58,720 --> 00:13:01,620
Bercouli: KID, YOU DON’T KNOW
WHAT YOU’RE TALKING ABOUT.

247
00:13:01,690 --> 00:13:05,630
YOU JUST SAID I "BECAME"
AN INTEGRITY KNIGHT.

248
00:13:05,690 --> 00:13:07,530
A KNIGHT’S ALL I’VE EVER BEEN.

249
00:13:07,600 --> 00:13:09,930
I DIDN’T HAVE A LIFE
BEFORE I WAS SUMMONED.

250
00:13:10,000 --> 00:13:13,030
Eugeo: AND THAT’S THE PART OF
YOU PEOPLE I FIND SO DESPICABLE!

251
00:13:13,100 --> 00:13:16,000
YOU’VE FORGOTTEN
WHO YOU USED TO BE.

252
00:13:16,070 --> 00:13:17,710
YOU’RE LOYAL TO THE AXIOM CHURCH

253
00:13:17,770 --> 00:13:19,710
WITHOUT KNOWING
WHAT IT REALLY IS.

254
00:13:19,770 --> 00:13:22,140
YOU ACT LIKE YOU’RE
CHAMPIONS OF JUSTICE,

255
00:13:22,210 --> 00:13:25,080
BUT YOU UPHOLD CORRUPTION!

256
00:13:25,150 --> 00:13:27,180
YOU THINK YOU’RE HERE
BECAUSE THE PONTIFEX

257
00:13:27,250 --> 00:13:29,950
SUMMONED YOU FROM HEAVEN,
\h\h\h\hBUT THAT’S A LIE!

258
00:13:30,020 --> 00:13:32,150
YOU HAD A MOTHER.

259
00:13:32,220 --> 00:13:34,120
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hSHE’S THE ONE
WHO GAVE YOU THE NAME BERCOULI.

260
00:13:34,190 --> 00:13:36,460
YOU’RE HUMAN, JUST LIKE ME!

261
00:13:36,520 --> 00:13:37,690
( gasps )

262
00:13:37,760 --> 00:13:41,960
BERCOULI. IN MY VILLAGE,
THEY TELL STORIES

263
00:13:42,030 --> 00:13:44,000
ABOUT HOW MUCH
OF A HERO YOU WERE.

264
00:13:44,070 --> 00:13:46,970
( Bercouli gasps )
WHAT STORIES?

265
00:13:47,040 --> 00:13:48,600
Eugeo: THINK BACK.

266
00:13:48,670 --> 00:13:51,410
\h\h\h\hI’M SURE YOU’VE
SEEN THIS SWORD BEFORE.

267
00:13:53,680 --> 00:13:56,510
\h\h\h\hBercouli:
YEAH, I HAVE, SOMEWHERE.

268
00:13:56,580 --> 00:13:59,450
RIGHT. YEARS AGO...

269
00:13:59,510 --> 00:14:02,480
IT WAS IN THE NEST
OF THE WHITE DRAGON.

270
00:14:02,550 --> 00:14:04,620
I SAW IT THERE
AFTER I KILLED IT.

271
00:14:04,690 --> 00:14:07,090
Eugeo: YOU KILLED THE DRAGON?

272
00:14:08,160 --> 00:14:10,230
I SAW ITS BONES...

273
00:14:10,290 --> 00:14:16,230
\h\h\h\hAND NOW--NOW YOU SAY
THE ONE WHO KILLED IT WAS YOU?

274
00:14:16,300 --> 00:14:19,430
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hA DRAGON
THAT PROTECTED THE HUMAN REALM,

275
00:14:19,500 --> 00:14:21,600
THE ONE FROM YOUR OWN LEGEND.

276
00:14:21,670 --> 00:14:24,940
DON’T YOU REMEMBER
ANYTHING ABOUT YOUR PAST,

277
00:14:25,010 --> 00:14:27,010
ABOUT WHO YOU WERE?

278
00:14:27,080 --> 00:14:31,050
IN RULID, THE VILLAGE YOU
FOUNDED AND WHERE I WAS BORN,

279
00:14:31,110 --> 00:14:32,510
EVERYONE KNEW ABOUT YOU.

280
00:14:32,580 --> 00:14:35,480
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hYOUNG OR OLD,
WE LOOKED UP TO YOU AS A HERO.

281
00:14:35,550 --> 00:14:38,990
\h\h\h\hBUT THE PONTIFEX
SEALED AWAY YOUR MEMORIES.

282
00:14:39,050 --> 00:14:43,320
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hSHE TURNED YOU
INTO THE FIRST INTEGRITY KNIGHT.

283
00:14:43,390 --> 00:14:45,130
THEN CAME THE OTHERS,

284
00:14:45,190 --> 00:14:49,960
EVERYONE FROM FANATIO TO ELDRIE,
EVEN ALICE,

285
00:14:50,030 --> 00:14:51,700
ALL OF YOU.

286
00:14:51,770 --> 00:14:55,240
BEFORE YOU BECAME
INTEGRITY KNIGHTS,

287
00:14:55,300 --> 00:14:56,440
YOU HAD LIVES.

288
00:14:56,500 --> 00:14:58,070
YOU WERE HUMAN.

289
00:14:58,140 --> 00:15:02,080
\h\h\h\hBercouli:
SEALED AWAY MY MEMORIES?

290
00:15:02,140 --> 00:15:08,020
I CAN’T JUST BELIEVE
A WILD STORY LIKE THAT.

291
00:15:08,080 --> 00:15:11,590
BUT ALL THAT STUFF I WAS TOLD

292
00:15:11,650 --> 00:15:15,260
ABOUT ME BEING SUMMONED
\h\h\h\hFROM HEAVEN,

293
00:15:15,320 --> 00:15:19,430
I HAD MY DOUBTS FOR A WHILE NOW.

294
00:15:19,490 --> 00:15:21,560
( Eugeo shudders )

295
00:15:26,730 --> 00:15:29,100
- ( bouncing )
- ( laughing )

296
00:15:29,170 --> 00:15:31,270
♪

297
00:15:36,540 --> 00:15:40,950
\h\h\h\hMan: WELL, WELL!
NOW, WHAT DO WE HAVE HERE?

298
00:15:42,120 --> 00:15:43,050
( chuckles )

299
00:15:43,120 --> 00:15:45,950
( laughing )

300
00:15:47,020 --> 00:15:49,360
THIS WON’T DO. NO, NO, NO.

301
00:15:49,420 --> 00:15:52,360
THIS WON’T DO AT ALL,
MY DEAR COMMANDER.

302
00:15:52,430 --> 00:15:57,070
SURELY, GOOD SIR, YOU DON’T PLAN
TO DIE ON US LIKE THIS?

303
00:15:57,130 --> 00:16:00,070
THAT WOULD BE TREASON
AGAINST HER EMINENCE,

304
00:16:00,130 --> 00:16:02,670
THE LOVELY PONTIFEX.

305
00:16:02,740 --> 00:16:05,070
\h\h\h\hIF SHE WERE AWAKE
TO SEE YOU IN THIS STATE,

306
00:16:05,140 --> 00:16:06,440
SHE WOULD BE LIVID.

307
00:16:06,510 --> 00:16:10,280
\h\h\h\hBercouli:
PRIME SENATOR CHUDELKIN,

308
00:16:10,350 --> 00:16:13,520
THIS IS A FIGHT
BETWEEN SWORDSMEN.

309
00:16:13,580 --> 00:16:16,950
A PIG LIKE YOU
HAS NO BUSINESS HERE.

310
00:16:17,020 --> 00:16:18,920
Chudelkin: HA HA HA!

311
00:16:18,990 --> 00:16:22,060
AFTER GOING SO EASY
ON THIS HERETIC,

312
00:16:22,120 --> 00:16:24,530
YOU HAVE NO BUSINESS
CORRECTING ME.

313
00:16:24,590 --> 00:16:27,400
DEAR COMMANDER, PRAY TELL,

314
00:16:27,460 --> 00:16:30,270
WHY DID YOU NOT USE
YOUR SWORD’S FULL POWER?

315
00:16:30,330 --> 00:16:33,500
IF YOU HAD, YOU COULD HAVE
SLAUGHTERED THIS LOATHSOME BRAT

316
00:16:33,570 --> 00:16:35,940
\h\h\h\hBEFORE HE OPENED
HIS SLANDEROUS LITTLE MOUTH.

317
00:16:36,000 --> 00:16:38,210
BUT YOU DID NOT, AND, THEREFORE,

318
00:16:38,270 --> 00:16:40,510
\h\h\h\hCOMMITTED TREASON
AGAINST THE GLORIOUS PONTIFEX.

319
00:16:40,580 --> 00:16:42,640
- Bercouli: SHUT YOUR MOUTH.
- ( Chudelkin gasps )

320
00:16:42,710 --> 00:16:47,220
Bercouli: I FOUGHT
WITH EVERYTHING I HAD.

321
00:16:48,320 --> 00:16:50,420
BUT YOU LIED TO ME.

322
00:16:50,490 --> 00:16:53,490
YOU LIED TO ALL OF US.

323
00:16:53,560 --> 00:16:59,330
THIS KID AIN’T NO ASSASSIN
FROM THE DARK TERRITORY.

324
00:16:59,390 --> 00:17:03,030
AND COMPARED TO AN UGLY
PIECE OF SHIT LIKE YOU--

325
00:17:03,100 --> 00:17:04,230
Chudelkin: SILENCE!

326
00:17:04,300 --> 00:17:06,600
BE SILENT, OR I’LL
RIP OFF YOUR HEAD!

327
00:17:08,340 --> 00:17:10,670
FOR YOUR INFORMATION, MY DEAR,

328
00:17:10,740 --> 00:17:12,410
WE WOULDN’T HAVE THIS PROBLEM

329
00:17:12,470 --> 00:17:15,440
IF YOU DAMNED KNIGHTS
WEREN’T SO DAMNED USELESS.

330
00:17:15,510 --> 00:17:18,410
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hHONESTLY,
WHEN HER EMINENCE AWAKES,

331
00:17:18,480 --> 00:17:21,020
YOU KNIGHTS WILL BE
THOROUGHLY PUNISHED.

332
00:17:21,080 --> 00:17:23,690
AT THE VERY LEAST, YOU AND
YOUR PRECIOUS VICE COMMANDER

333
00:17:23,750 --> 00:17:25,650
SHALL BE REPROCESSED.

334
00:17:25,720 --> 00:17:27,360
Bercouli: "RE-" WHAT?

335
00:17:27,420 --> 00:17:29,960
YOU’RE TALKIN’ OUT
YOUR ASS AGAIN.

336
00:17:30,020 --> 00:17:31,160
( Chudelkin chuckles )

337
00:17:31,230 --> 00:17:34,100
SYSTEM CALL! DEEP FREEZE!

338
00:17:34,160 --> 00:17:39,230
INTEGRATOR UNIT I.D.
ZERO-ZERO-ONE!

339
00:17:43,070 --> 00:17:44,940
( Bercouli gasps )

340
00:17:48,010 --> 00:17:49,110
( Eugeo gasping )

341
00:17:51,180 --> 00:17:53,580
( Chudelkin laughs )

342
00:17:53,650 --> 00:17:56,280
\h\h\h\hWE DON’T NEED
OLD FARTS LIKE NUMBER ONE

343
00:17:56,350 --> 00:17:58,590
STINKING UP THE PLACE ANYMORE.

344
00:17:58,650 --> 00:18:00,720
NOW WE HAVE A MUCH YOUNGER,

345
00:18:00,790 --> 00:18:02,420
- MORE USEFUL PAWN...
- Eugeo: KIRITO.

346
00:18:02,490 --> 00:18:04,460
Chudelkin: AT OUR DISPOSAL.

347
00:18:04,530 --> 00:18:06,160
Eugeo: ALICE.

348
00:18:08,400 --> 00:18:09,560
Kirito: EUGEO.

349
00:18:09,630 --> 00:18:11,470
Alice: IS SOMETHING THE MATTER?

350
00:18:11,530 --> 00:18:14,140
Kirito: HUH? OH, NO. NOTHING.

351
00:18:14,200 --> 00:18:16,000
AS SOON AS THE MOON COMES OUT,

352
00:18:16,070 --> 00:18:18,470
I THINK WE CAN START
CLIMBING UP THE WALL AGAIN.

353
00:18:18,540 --> 00:18:20,140
LONG AS I CAN MAKE SPIKES,

354
00:18:20,210 --> 00:18:22,210
IT SHOULD GO PRETTY EASY
\h\h\h\hFROM HERE ON.

355
00:18:22,280 --> 00:18:24,380
THERE’S NO MINIONS ABOVE US,

356
00:18:24,450 --> 00:18:26,650
AND THE OTHERS HERE
AIN’T WAKING UP.

357
00:18:26,710 --> 00:18:29,580
FOR NOW. BESIDES THE LACK
\h\h\h\hOF SACRED POWER,

358
00:18:29,650 --> 00:18:32,190
THE ONLY OTHER BIG PROBLEM
IS FOOD.

359
00:18:32,250 --> 00:18:34,360
I DON’T KNOW ABOUT YOU,
BUT I’M STARVING.

360
00:18:34,420 --> 00:18:36,690
\h\h\h\hIF I THINK ABOUT
HOW MUCH FURTHER WE GOTTA GO,

361
00:18:36,760 --> 00:18:38,290
MY HEAD STARTS SPINNING.

362
00:18:38,360 --> 00:18:41,100
\h\h\h\hAlice: COULD YOU BE
ANY MORE OF A DISAPPOINTMENT?

363
00:18:41,160 --> 00:18:42,230
Kirito: WHAT?!

364
00:18:42,300 --> 00:18:43,930
Alice: WHETHER WE MISS
\h\h\h\hA MEAL OR TWO

365
00:18:44,000 --> 00:18:47,000
IS THE LEAST OF OUR WORRIES,
UNLESS YOU ARE A CHILD.

366
00:18:47,070 --> 00:18:49,670
\h\h\h\hKirito: YEAH, WELL,
TECHNICALLY, I STILL SORT OF AM.

367
00:18:49,740 --> 00:18:52,040
I MIGHT NOT ACT
LIKE IT ALL THE TIME,

368
00:18:52,110 --> 00:18:54,240
BUT I’M NOT EVEN
OUT OF MY TEENS YET.

369
00:18:54,310 --> 00:18:56,310
I DON’T EAT, MY LIFE GOES DOWN,

370
00:18:56,380 --> 00:18:58,180
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hA PROBLEM
YOU BADASS KNIGHTS DON’T HAVE.

371
00:18:58,250 --> 00:18:59,680
Alice: SUCH LANGUAGE!

372
00:18:59,750 --> 00:19:02,150
EVEN INTEGRITY KNIGHTS
\h\h\h\hGET HUNGRY.

373
00:19:02,220 --> 00:19:04,520
\h\h\h\hWE MUST EAT,
OR WE LOSE LIFE LIKE YOU.

374
00:19:04,590 --> 00:19:06,250
- ( stomach grumbles )
- ( both gasp )

375
00:19:08,190 --> 00:19:09,120
( Kirito snickers )

376
00:19:09,190 --> 00:19:10,430
WHOA! HOLD ON!

377
00:19:10,490 --> 00:19:12,290
SORRY! I WAS KIDDING!

378
00:19:12,360 --> 00:19:16,300
OF COURSE YOU GET HUNGRY.
YOU’RE AS ALIVE AS ANYONE ELSE.

379
00:19:16,360 --> 00:19:19,530
\h\h\h\hSPEAKIN’ OF FOOD,
WHERE ARE CARDINAL’S SNACKS?

380
00:19:19,600 --> 00:19:21,040
Alice: HMM?

381
00:19:21,100 --> 00:19:24,110
\h\h\h\hKirito: AW, YEAH.
I KNEW I SNAGGED SOME MORE.

382
00:19:24,170 --> 00:19:25,440
LOOKIT! IT’S DINNERTIME!

383
00:19:25,510 --> 00:19:27,110
♪

384
00:19:27,180 --> 00:19:28,540
Alice: WHY IN THE WORLD

385
00:19:28,610 --> 00:19:31,210
WOULD YOU STORE YOUR FOOD
\h\h\h\hIN SUCH A WAY?

386
00:19:31,280 --> 00:19:34,180
Kirito: I DON’T. I JUST TAPPED
MY POCKET, AND THERE THEY WERE.

387
00:19:34,250 --> 00:19:36,080
TRY IT SOMETIME.

388
00:19:36,150 --> 00:19:38,320
BUT FIRST I GOTTA
GET THESE READY TO EAT.

389
00:19:38,390 --> 00:19:39,350
( chuckles )

390
00:19:39,420 --> 00:19:40,420
( Alice groans )

391
00:19:40,490 --> 00:19:42,260
Kirito: SYSTEM CALL.

392
00:19:42,320 --> 00:19:44,490
GENERATE THERMAL ELEMENT.

393
00:19:44,560 --> 00:19:45,490
BURST ELE--

394
00:19:45,560 --> 00:19:46,660
Alice: NO, YOU FOOL!

395
00:19:46,730 --> 00:19:48,200
Kirito: WHAT?

396
00:19:48,260 --> 00:19:50,530
Alice: IF YOU USE THAT ART,
YOU WILL BURN THEM!

397
00:19:50,600 --> 00:19:52,300
Kirito: SORRY.

398
00:19:52,370 --> 00:19:54,070
( gasps )

399
00:19:56,500 --> 00:19:59,040
Alice: GENERATE THERMAL ELEMENT,

400
00:19:59,110 --> 00:20:00,710
AQUEOUS ELEMENT,

401
00:20:00,780 --> 00:20:02,640
AERIAL ELEMENT.

402
00:20:04,280 --> 00:20:07,380
VORTEX SHAPE. BURST.

403
00:20:08,450 --> 00:20:10,150
( steam hissing )

404
00:20:10,220 --> 00:20:11,950
Kirito: WHOA!

405
00:20:12,020 --> 00:20:13,090
HURRY! GIMME ONE!

406
00:20:13,150 --> 00:20:14,620
( Alice chuckles )

407
00:20:14,690 --> 00:20:16,020
Kirito: WAIT! NO, NO, NO!

408
00:20:16,090 --> 00:20:17,190
Alice: I AM JOKING.

409
00:20:18,260 --> 00:20:19,960
( Kirito chuckles )

410
00:20:20,030 --> 00:20:21,960
( blows )

411
00:20:23,030 --> 00:20:24,330
MMM.

412
00:20:24,400 --> 00:20:26,230
THAT HIT THE SPOT.

413
00:20:26,300 --> 00:20:27,500
THANKS FOR SHOWING ME THAT.

414
00:20:27,570 --> 00:20:29,340
I DIDN’T KNOW
YOU COULD STEAM FOOD

415
00:20:29,400 --> 00:20:31,010
USING ELEMENTS
INSTEAD OF A PAN.

416
00:20:31,070 --> 00:20:33,580
\h\h\h\hDID YOU TEACH
YOUR LITTLE SIS HOW TO COOK?

417
00:20:33,640 --> 00:20:35,510
’CAUSE SELKA’S
REALLY GOOD AT IT.

418
00:20:35,580 --> 00:20:36,610
( gasps )

419
00:20:36,680 --> 00:20:38,680
Alice: WHAT DID
YOU SAY JUST NOW?

420
00:20:38,750 --> 00:20:40,210
( Kirito gasps )

421
00:20:41,320 --> 00:20:43,590
THAT YOU HAVE A LITTLE SISTER.

422
00:20:43,650 --> 00:20:46,150
HER NAME’S SELKA.

423
00:20:46,220 --> 00:20:47,390
Alice: SISTER?

424
00:20:49,090 --> 00:20:51,530
♪

425
00:20:51,590 --> 00:20:53,130
( gasps )

426
00:20:53,190 --> 00:20:55,030
Kirito: I CAN
TELL YOU ABOUT HER.

427
00:20:55,100 --> 00:20:58,770
I CAN TELL YOU EVERYTHING
I KNOW ABOUT THIS PLACE.

428
00:20:58,830 --> 00:21:01,040
\h\h\h\hI DON’T KNOW
IF YOU’LL BELIEVE ME,

429
00:21:01,100 --> 00:21:02,240
BUT IT’S WORTH A SHOT.

430
00:21:03,710 --> 00:21:05,010
( Alice sighs )

431
00:21:05,070 --> 00:21:07,540
GO ON, THEN.

432
00:21:07,610 --> 00:21:09,080
HOWEVER...

433
00:21:09,140 --> 00:21:13,180
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hIF I DETECT EVEN
A TRACE OF DECEIT IN YOUR WORDS,

434
00:21:13,250 --> 00:21:15,950
I SHALL END YOUR LIFE.

435
00:21:16,020 --> 00:21:17,220
( Kirito gasps )

436
00:21:19,290 --> 00:21:22,190
Singer: ♪ OH, EVERYTHING
TURNS TO ASH, TO ASH ♪

437
00:21:22,260 --> 00:21:24,190
( singing in Japanese )

438
00:21:31,700 --> 00:21:35,200
\h\h\h\h♪ AND EVERYTHING
TURNS TO DUST, TO DUST ♪

439
00:21:35,270 --> 00:21:37,210
( singing in Japanese )

440
00:21:44,810 --> 00:22:02,430
♪ FORGET-ME-NOT

